📦 Backend README
Language Learning Platform – Backend

This is the backend API for the Language Learning Platform.
It handles courses, lessons, quizzes, flashcards, authentication, and streak tracking using Node.js, Express, and Supabase.

🚀 Tech Stack

Node.js

Express.js

Supabase (Database)

CORS

REST API

📂 Project Structure
Backend
│
├── routes
│   ├── auth.js
│   ├── courses.js
│   ├── lessons.js
│   ├── quiz.js
│   ├── flashcardRoutes.js
│   └── streakRoutes.js
│
├── supabaseClient.js
├── server.js
├── package.json
└── .env
⚙️ Installation

1️⃣ Clone the repository

git clone https://github.com/your-repo/language-learning-platform.git

2️⃣ Go to backend folder

cd Backend

3️⃣ Install dependencies

npm install
🔑 Environment Variables

Create a .env file.

Example:

SUPABASE_URL=your_supabase_url
SUPABASE_KEY=your_supabase_key
PORT=5000
▶️ Run the Server
node server.js

Server runs on:

http://localhost:5000
📡 API Endpoints
Authentication
POST /api/auth/signup
POST /api/auth/login
Courses
GET /courses

Fetch all language courses.

Lessons
GET /lessons/:courseId

Fetch lessons for a course.

Quiz
GET /quiz/:lessonId
POST /quiz

Fetch quiz questions or create quiz.

Flashcards
GET /api/flashcards/random

Fetch random flashcards.

🔥 Streak System

Tracks user learning streak.

Get streak
GET /streaks/:userId

Example:

https://your-backend-url/streaks/1
Update streak (after quiz)
POST /streaks/update

Body:

{
  "userId": 1
}

This increases the streak when the user completes a quiz.

🗄 Database (Supabase)

Tables used:

users

courses

lessons

quiz

flashcards

streaks

Example streak table:

id
user_id
current_streak
last_login
🧠 How Streak Works

User completes a quiz

Frontend calls

POST /streaks/update

Backend checks:

If user has no streak → create streak

If last login is not today → increase streak

If already updated today → no change
